<emphasis id="F788EAA53645800DDA065CF9FB8C5CD9" box="[1065,1132,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">stylus</emphasis>
) (Latin, masculine) = stilletto, stylet. Used as a noun in apposition and referring to the rather unique morphology of the gonostylus with its crablike shape and ventrally produced, heavily setose lobe.
</paragraph>
